{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Cupid enrichment op: LLM ticket-digest extractor + digest schema\n\n## Why\nSemantic overlap detection needs a compact, normalized per-ticket representation that catches paraphrase (\"login broken\" vs \"users can't authenticate\") WITHOUT embeddings, keeping rebar on its Anthropic-only, no-heavy-ML grain. The Cupid pattern (arXiv:2308.10022) uses the LLM as a one-time feature extractor. DERISKED: the recall spike (see epic experiment comment) showed digest-BM25F retrieves 8/8 heavy paraphrases at rank 1 (recall@20 = 1.0), so this digest is the load-bearing artifact of the whole feature.\n\n## What\nA new LLM operation `rebar.llm.enrich(ticket_id)` returning a validated dedup digest, plus its output schema and prompt. Modeled on `src/rebar/llm/completion.py` (assemble context â†’ load prompt â†’ `RunRequest(mode=\"structured\", execution_mode=\"single_turn\")` â†’ validate) â€” NOT on `operations.py::review_ticket`, which uses `mode=\"findings\"`/`execution_mode=\"agentic\"` (the opposite of what we want).\n\nDigest schema (`ticket_digest`): `{problem_keywords: string[], component_or_area: string, key_entities: string[], propositions: string[]}`; `propositions` = 2â€“6 atomic problem/repro statements; logs/stack-traces/code discarded by the prompt. Deterministic payload (no timestamps/uuids) so the stored record is stable modulo LLM wording.\n\n## Config-bound threading (resolves the zero-arg-builder gap)\nThe proposition bound is NOT enforced through the `register_contract` schema builder (it is a zero-arg `Callable[[], type]` that cannot see config). Instead: (a) the prompt instructs the model to emit MIN..MAX propositions, and (b) the op post-validates the parsed count: if the model returns MORE than max, truncate to max; if FEWER than min, keep them and set `low_proposition_count=True` on the OP'S RETURN object `{digest: <ticket_digest>, low_proposition_count: bool}` â€” the flag is on the op return, NOT a 5th field of the persisted `ticket_digest` (which stays exactly its four fields); never raise. Bounds live on `LLMConfig` (`[tool.rebar.llm]`, env `REBAR_LLM_OVERLAP_PROPOSITIONS_MIN/MAX`, read in `LLMConfig.from_env`) â€” the LLM-tunable layer; `_config_schema.py` reserves `llm.*` so these must NOT go on `VerifyConfig`.\n\n## Scope (exact edit targets)\n- Config field target: `src/rebar/llm/config.py` (`LLMConfig.overlap_propositions_min/max`, `from_env`).\n- New op module `src/rebar/llm/enrich.py`; export `enrich` from `src/rebar/llm/__init__.py` (NOT `src/rebar/__init__.py`; core must not import `rebar.llm`).\n- Prompt `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/enrich.md`, front-matter `execution_mode: single_turn`, `outputs: ticket_digest`, no `category` (it is a prompt-classification flag like `\"review\"`; omit for enrich) (valid execution_mode enum is `single_turn|agentic` per `prompts.py:74`; `1-TURN` is invalid).\n- Output schema `src/rebar/schemas/ticket_digest.schema.json` (field-level: all four fields required; arrays of non-empty strings; `propositions` minItems 1); register in `src/rebar/llm/contracts.py` via `register_contract(\"ticket_digest\", <builder>)` â€” the builder lives beside the op in `enrich.py`.\n- `LLMConfig` (`src/rebar/llm/config.py`): add `overlap_propositions_min` (default 2) / `overlap_propositions_max` (default 6) to the `from_env` key set.\n\n## Dependencies\nNone (leaf). S2/S5/S7 consume this op + the `ticket_digest` schema (they are sibling stories; the grep-the-codebase reviewer will not see them until they land).\n\n## Testing\n- Unit `tests/unit/test_enrich.py`: `test_schema_valid` (payload validates), `test_logs_excluded` (stack-trace frames absent from digest), `test_no_nondeterministic_fields`, `test_propositions_bounded` (>max truncated to max; <min sets low_proposition_count flag, no raise), `test_bad_json` (FakeRunner malformed â†’ clean error, no partial write), `test_absent_llm` (raises cleanly).\n- Quality check as a PYTEST FIXTURE test (NOT the prompt-eval harness, which needs a registered deterministic scorer that does not exist for the `ticket_digest` shape): `test_enrich_quality` over â‰¥6 labeled tickets (fixtures at `tests/fixtures/enrich_quality/`, each with a GOLD set of expected entities/keywords, incl. a ~4000-token body): DETERMINISTIC assertion that â‰¥1 gold entity/keyword per ticket appears in `key_entities âˆª problem_keywords` (string-set membership, not a subjective 'names the core problem' judgement). Proving command: `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_enrich.py -q`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `rebar.llm.enrich(ticket_id)` returns a `ticket_digest`-valid payload; `pytest tests/unit/test_enrich.py::test_schema_valid`.\n- [ ] Logs/stack-traces/code excluded; `::test_logs_excluded`.\n- [ ] Payload has no nondeterministic fields; `::test_no_nondeterministic_fields`.\n- [ ] `propositions` count enforced in the op (>max truncate, <min flag, no raise); `::test_propositions_bounded`.\n- [ ] Malformed structured output â†’ tolerant-parse clean error, no partial write; `::test_bad_json`. Absent-LLM â†’ clean raise; `::test_absent_llm`.\n- [ ] Quality fixture test `test_enrich_quality` (â‰¥6 labeled tickets) asserts â‰¥1 gold entity/keyword appears in `key_entities âˆª problem_keywords` (deterministic string-set membership); `pytest tests/unit/test_enrich.py::test_enrich_quality`.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783627437080484001,"uuid":"a458f4a1-8f57-477c-a8dc-18e45bbc764e"}